  "texts": [
    "in Q,(4.11)∂ t σ α -∆σ α = -χ ∆φ α -P (σ α + χ (1 -φ α) -µ α) + u 2 a.e.",
    "in Q,(4.12)µ α (0) = µ 0,α, (∂ t µ α)(0) = µ ′ 0,α, φ α (0) = φ 0, σ(0) = σ 0,α a.e. in Ω.",
    "(4.13)Then there exists a quadruple (µ, φ, ξ, σ) such that, for some subsequence α k tending to 0, there holds µ α k → µ weakly star in L ∞ (0, T; V), (4.14) α k µ α k → 0 weakly star in W 2,∞ (0, T; V *) and strongly in W 1,∞ (0, T; H), (4.15) φ α k → φ weakly star in W 1,∞ (0, T; H) ∩ H 1 (0, T; V) ∩ L ∞ (0, T; W) and strongly in C 0 ([0, T]; V) ∩ C 0 (Q), (4.16) ξ α k → ξ weakly star in L ∞ (0, T; H), (4.17)σ α k → σ weakly star in H 1 (0, T; H) ∩ L ∞ (0, T; V) ∩ L 2 (0, T; W).",
    "(4.18)Moreover, (µ, φ, ξ, σ) is a solution to the viscous Cahn-Hilliard systemΩ ∂ t φ v + Ω ∇µ • ∇v = Ω P (σ + χ (1 -φ) -µ)v - Ω h(φ)u 1 vfor every v ∈ V and a.e.",
